            <biogHist>
                <p>Malcolm MacLeod was born in Lochmaddy, North Uist, the son of John MacLeod,
                    seaman, and Ann n√©e Munrow. In 1831 he married Ann MacKinnon and in the 1841
                    census he is listed as a Shipmaster in Heiskeir, North Uist at the time. By the
                    time of the 1851 census, he is called a Postmaster and is in Lochmaddy with his
                    wife and their five children, his mother-in-law, a granddaughter and five
                    servants. In 1861, his wife Ann is listed as a ship owner's wife. By 1871 the
                    couple are to be found in Lochmaddy together with two of their sons and Malcolm
                    noted as a retired Master Mariner. </p>
                <p>He died in 1872 in Lochmaddy and his cousin Malcolm MacQuien witnessed the
                    certificate; his wife survived him by 21 years, dying in Glasgow in 1893. </p>
